<s> [INST] You are an expert in Natural Language Inference (NLI). Please list all possible explanations why the the following statement is undetermined (neutral) given the context below without introductory phrases. 
Context: When he's ready for a major strike, how many innocents do you suppose are going to suffer? To quote one of your contemporaries; 'The needs of the many outweigh the needs of the few.' ' 
Statement: If he does a big strike, many people will suffer. 
Answer: [/INST] 1. The statement may be referring to a different group of people than the context.
2. The term "big strike" in the statement might not mean the same as "major strike" in the context.
3. The "many people" in the statement might not include "innocents" as mentioned in the context.
4. The statement does not specify whether the many people suffering is due to the actions of the few or not.
5. The statement does not indicate whether the suffering is justified or not, whereas the context implies that it might not be.
6. The statement does not provide information on the severity of the suffering, while the context implies that it could be significant.
7. The statement does not specify if the "many people" are part of "the many" or "the few" mentioned in the context.
8. The statement does not indicate if the speaker agrees or disagrees with the principle of "the needs of the many outweigh the needs of the few".</s>